reviews.text: Really nice cafe in Sai Ying Pun. The place is cool and the people working there are nice and helpful. Coffees and the food offered are quite good. Quiet place where you can easily work or chat with a friend or just take something to go. Like their stance on plastic as well. Recommended.
Great coffee and great staff. Food choices are well rounded and very tasty. Will be back.
Good quiet cafe unfortunately the WiFi is not stable. Writing this review in the cafe using my mobile hotspot.

Yummy tuna puttanesca and Teapigs Jasmine tea outside in the courtyard. Very yum! Heard that service can be slow but I think I missed the rush and my food came really quickly. Really nice staff who are friendly and helpful! Thank you Open Door!
A popular neighborhood cafe serving comfort food and drinks.

result.name: CHI Residences 120

reviews.text: Big rooms with good amenities. Close to the metro. Kitchen is a little strange with the elevator and exit sign but does the job

Stunning view! The biggest and spacious 1BR with balcony serviced apartment in HK I found. Lots of cupboard space. Very accessible to the pier if you're in and out of Macau. Nice walk path along the harbour to Central. Lovely team of staff 😘

it is located a walk distance from the station.
but I'm extremly satisfied with the facility.

especially, we could cook with cooktop. it was good because we had a children.
and when I told the serviceperson that the room is a little cold, then he brought a portable heater.

We'll stay at this residence if we visit there again.
Didn't really blow me away
